Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Located in the middle of Perth’s most iconic and picturesque streets, Unit 8 / 25- 35 Mends Street, South Perth is surrounded by prominent food & beverage operators, fashion retailers and local amenities, benefiting from the expansion in residential development and population growth.   

Offering 88sqm* of multi-use capability, this first floor re-furbished tenancy has freshly painted walls, split-cycle air-conditioning, suspended ceilings, storage options and CCTV security. 

The unique tenancy is the perfect entry level Office, Retail or QSR opportunity for a new/established business to join the transformation of South Perth. 
 
Additional features include:

+ 2 Car-parking bays 
+ Mends street exposure
+ Fascia signage 
+ Multiple uses (Subject to Council Approval)
+ Popular retail/shopping precinct
+ 100m to Windsor Hotel
+ 200m to South Perth foreshore 
+ 300m to Perth Zoo
+ Surrounded by prominent local amenity

Zoning:

This property is zoned ‘Mends Street Centre Commercial’ under the City of South Perth’s Local Town Planning Scheme No.6. 

For further information or to arrange an inspection, please contact the Leasing Agent.

* Approx
* Subject to Council Approval

Common.Strapline.Common.Text: MULTI-PURPOSE OPPORTUNITY IN THE HEART OF SOUTH PERTH

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text:
Classic waterfront setting in the Old Perth Port precinct of Elizabeth Quay and Barrack Street Jetty. Established passing trade from the Lucky Shag Bar and the South Perth ferry terminal, along with huge increase in traffic since the completion of the new landscaped Bell Tower precinct, and commencement of Perth Water Taxi terminal immediately at the site.

This is the only restaurant site in the precinct with a full 270 degree genuine views including Perth City Skyline, taking in the Elizabeth Quay area, Kings Park profile, the full expanse of Swan River including South Perth foreshore, Heirisson Island and the Burswood complex, as well as Langley Park and East Perth foreshore areas.

*Approx.

Prime CBD retail tenancies have become available along the busy Hay Street Mall. Join a long list of strong national operators and enjoy maximum exposure and high daily footfall in the heart of Perth.

THE OPPORTUNITIES:

SHOPS 6&7 - CNR OF HAY ST & WILLIAM ST - 134m2*
The location doesn't get much better than this! Corner tenancy with large frontage facing both the Hay St Mall and the busy William St. Fantastic public transport access and only a stone's throw from the Murray Street Mall with Forrest Chase and Raine Square. 

SHOP 3 - HAY STREET MALL - 144m2*
Nestled in the midst of national retailers including T2 Tea, Solid Gold Diamonds, OPSM and Novo Shoes just to name a few, this aptly sized tenancy is ideally suited to a number of uses from service retail to fashion and more.

For further enquiries and to arrange an inspection, contact CBRE's dedicated leasing team
